Android has the [`@VisibleForTesting`][1] annotation from `android.support.annotation` package.

&gt; The `@VisibleForTesting` annotation indicates that an annotated method is more visible than normally necessary to make the method testable. This annotation has an optional `otherwise` argument that lets you designate what the visibility of the method should have been if not for the need to make it visible for testing. Lint uses the `otherwise` argument to enforce the intended visibility.

In practice, it means that you should make a method open for testing and the `@VisibleForTesting` annotation will show a warning.

